The paper discusses a technique for the fusion of multiple sources of information and the evaluation and selection of alternatives under multi-criteria. This involves assigning differing importance to criteria and finding a consensus of the opinion of multiple experts. These topics are commonly discussed in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), social and information networks (cs.SI), computer engineering (cs.CE), and software engineering (cs.SE).
